OL,3,C'It's hard to see light at the end of
OL,4,Cthe tunnel': Inside HMP Highpoint
OL,6,FBut in his new role, his view seems to
OL,7,Fhave shifted. Pushed on whether he
OL,8,Freally believes building more prisons
OL,9,Fis the way out of this crisis, he
OL,10,Fsaid: "We unfortunately need to build
OL,11,Flots more prison places.
OL,13,F"That's why we're going to build
OL,14,F14,000, because the prison population
OL,15,Fis going up by 100 people a week."
OL,17,FAsked if he still has a target for how
OL,18,Fmany people shouldn't be in prison, he
OL,19,Freplied: "No, there's a target in my
OL,20,Fmind of building more prisons."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
